1. e4 c5 2. Nc3 Nc6 3. f4 d6 4. Nf3 Nf6 5. Bc4 g6 6. d3 Bg7 7. O-O O-O 8. Qe1 e6 9. f5 { We play f5 anyway! } 9... exf5 10. Qh4 h6 11. Bxh6 Nh5 { Pause. } 12. Bg5 Qd7 { Nelson suggests bringing in more pieces. In particular, one that could aim at a juicy square after some exchanges. } 13. Nd5 fxe4 { Nelson spends hours discussing a crazy line. } 14. dxe4 Qg4 15. Qxg4 Bxg4 { There was, and still is, a potential free pawn. Do you see it? } 16. Ne7+ Nxe7 17. Bxe7 Rfe8 18. Bxd6 b6 { Is anything hanging? } 19. c3 { Can they take on e4? } 19... Rad8 20. e5 { Ng5 was best but this works too. } 20... Bxf3 21. Rxf3 Bxe5 22. Bxf7+ Kg7 23. Bxe8 Rxe8 24. Bxe5+ Rxe5 25. Raf1 Re7 { Do you see it? } 26. g4 *


